  <modalFeedback identifier="CORRECT_FEEDBACK" outcomeIdentifier="GENERAL_FEEDBACK" showHide="show">
    <p>
      <b>Option B (Prolonged prothrombin time) is correct.</b>
      Although Vitamin K is needed for all these factors, a deficiency would be evident first in the increased prothrombin time because Factor VII is the most vulnerable here with its short half-life. Prolonged deficiency would also affect the other factors and could increase the PTT but factors VIIIa and IXa are robust factors in the clotting cascade and any increase would not be marked.
    </p>
